                                team was using Sketch, which required complex, nested
                                symbol architectures. It was very difficult to use
                                and to maintain as our system grew.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Cross-Platform Collaboration:</strong> Customer
                                Success managers and external partners increasingly
                                needed to view our prototypes. Sketch being Mac-only
                                and prototypes being more difficult to access created
                                major blockers for them.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Internal UX Survey:</strong> A team survey
                                showed a 9-to-4 preference for Figma. Designers highlighted
                                its cleaner interface, faster prototyping capabilities,
                                and browser-based collaboration.
                            </li>
